tempean.d:
a. Of or pertaining to Temple, a valley in Thessaly,
   celebrated by Greek poets on account of its beautiful scenery;
   resembling Temple; hence, beautiful; delightful; charming.

termless.d:
a. Having no term or end; unlimited; boundless; unending;
   as, termless time.
a. Inexpressible; indescribable.

testudinarious.d:
a. Of or pertaining to the shell of a tortoise;
   resembling a tortoise shell; having the color or markings of a tortoise
   shell.

tetrachord.d:
n. A scale series of four sounds, of which the extremes,
   or first and last, constituted a fourth. These extremes were immutable;
   the two middle sounds were changeable.
